'''Michael Joseph "Spike" Albrecht''' (born August 24, 1992<ref name="MGoBlue bio">{{cite web|title=Spike Albrecht Bio|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-baskbl/mtt/spike_albrecht_817179.html|publisher=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=April 9, 2013}}</ref>) is a [[college basketball]] [[point guard]] for [[Michigan Wolverines men's basketball]]. He is playing his [[sophomore]] season for the [[2013<U+2013>14 Michigan Wolverines men's basketball team|2013<U+2013>14 team]].  Spike played high school basketball in his hometown of [[Crown Point, Indiana]].<ref name="High school bio">{{cite web|title=Spike Albrecht HS|url=http://www.maxpreps.com/athletes/Os2gLzgsfEGOS9YzpT3I_A/basketball-winter-11-12/athlete_notes-spike-albrecht.htm|publisher=MaxPreps.com|accessdate=April 9, 2013}}</ref> He is most well known for his 17-point first half performance off the bench (video below) for the [[2012<U+2013>13 Michigan Wolverines men's basketball team|2012<U+2013>13 team]] in the championship game of the [[2013 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament]].

==Early life==
At age 5, Michael Albrecht, son of Tammy and Charles "Chuck" Albrecht,<ref name=SAitsNcM/> received his first [[Cleat (shoe)|baseball spikes]] and refused to take them off, earning his now famous nickname.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/ncaab-the-dagger/did-spike-albrecht-nickname-024559363--ncaab.html|title=How did Spike Albrecht get his nickname?|accessdate=2014-01-30|date=2013-04-08|publisher=[[Yahoo! Sports]]|author=Kudak, Kevin}}</ref> Chuck now runs a summer basketball camp that Spike assists at.<ref name=HSArttncaU/> Albrecht attended Taft Middle School in Crown Point before attending [[Crown Point High School]] where he averaged 21 points, 5 assists, 3 steals and 4 rebounds as a [[Senior (education)|senior]] in 2011.<ref name=HSArttncaU>{{cite web|url=http://posttrib.suntimes.com/sports/20848225-556/hutton-spike-albrecht-ready-to-tackle-next-challenge-at-um.html|title=HUTTON: Spike Albrecht ready to tackle next challenge at UM|accessdate=2014-01-30|date=2013-06-19|work=[[Post-Tribune]]|author=Hutton, Mike}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://posttrib.suntimes.com/sports/highschools/11759573-556/crown-points-albrecht-commits-to-michigan.html|title=Crown Point's Albrecht commits to Michigan |accessdate=2012-04-07|date=2012-04-06|author=Osipoff, Michael|work=[[Post-Tribune]]}}</ref> Albrecht committed to Michigan on April 6, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/#!/GoodmanCBS/status/188426015146639361|title=@GoodmanCBS status|accessdate=2012-04-07|date=2012-04-06|publisher=[[Twitter]]}}</ref> Albrecht led [[Northfield Mount Hermon School]] to the 2012 [[New England Preparatory School Athletic Council]] (NEPSAC) Class AAA Boys' Basketball Tournament, defeating future Michigan teammate [[Mitch McGary]]'s [[Brewster Academy]] in the semifinals. Albrecht was awarded the [[Most Valuable Player]] (MVP) of the tournament. Albrecht was a former [[Amateur Athletic Union]] (AAU) teammate of McGary and future Michigan teammate [[Glenn Robinson III]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.annarbor.com/sports/um-basketball/michigan-basketball-picks-up-2012-commitment-from-prep-school-point-guard-spike-albrecht/|title=Michigan basketball picks up 2012 commitment from prep school point guard Spike Albrecht|accessdate=2012-04-07|date=2012-04-06|work=[[AnnArbor.com]]|author=Baumgardner, Nick}}</ref> Albrecht's and outgoing (when Albrech was an incoming [[freshman]]) captain [[Zack Novak]]'s fathers were collegiate teammates.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nwitimes.com/sports/fathers-will-backs-sons-as-rivals-during-sectional/article_bba37b0d-7ef6-5180-ae68-00aec159fb03.html|title=Fathers will backs sons as rivals during sectional|accessdate=2012-04-07|date=2008-02-26|work=[[Northwest Indiana Times]]|author=Hanlon, Steve}}</ref>
