| alt2      = 
| caption2  = 
}}
In Albrecht's role with the [[2012<U+2013>13 Michigan Wolverines men's basketball team|2012<U+2013>13 Wolverines team]], he never scored more than 7 points in a game before the NCAA Tournament.<ref name=LoMtwnc/> In the regional finals on March 31 against [[2012<U+2013>13 Florida Gators men's basketball team|Florida]], Michigan built a 13<U+2013>0 lead and never led by less than 10 the rest of the game.<ref name=MrFert1FFbs1>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=330900057|title=Michigan routs Florida en route to 1st Final Four berth since 1993|accessdate=2013-03-31|date=2013-03-31|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=330900057|title=(4) Michigan 79 (30<U+2013>7, 12<U+2013>6 Big Ten); (3) Florida 59 (29<U+2013>8, 14<U+2013>4 SEC)|accessdate=2013-03-31|date=2013-03-31|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> Several players had career-highs in the game, including Albrecht who had 7 points and 3 steals.<ref name=PNM7F5>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/033113aap.html|title=Postgame Notes: #10 Michigan 79, #14 Florida 59|accessdate=2013-03-31|date=2013-03-31|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=MGoBlue.com}}</ref> The national championship rounds were held at the [[Georgia Dome]] in [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. In the April 6 national semifinal against [[2012<U+2013>13 Syracuse Orange men's basketball team|Syracuse]], Michigan emerged with its thirty-first victory, the most since the [[1992<U+2013>93 Michigan Wolverines men's basketball team|1992<U+2013>93 team]] went 31<U+2013>5. The bench contributed 22 points, including 6 from Albrecht, who raised his NCAA tournament total to 5-for-5 on three-point shots.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=330960130|title=(4) Syracuse 56 (30<U+2013>10, 11<U+2013>7 Big East); (4) Michigan 61 (31<U+2013>7, 12<U+2013>6 Big Ten)|accessdate=2013-04-07|date=2013-04-06|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/040713aaf.html|title=Postgame Notes: #10 Michigan 61, #16 Syracuse 56|accessdate=2013-04-07|date=2013-04-07|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=MGoBlue.com}}</ref>

Michigan advanced to the April 8, [[2013 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament]] championship game where the team lost to Midwest number one seed [[2012<U+2013>13 Louisville Cardinals men's basketball team|Louisville]] by an 82&ndash;76 margin despite 17 points, including 4-for-5 [[three-point shot|three-point shooting]], from Albrecht in the game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=330980097|title=(4) Michigan 76 (31-8, 12-6 Big Ten); (1) Louisville 82 (35-5, 14-4 Big East)|accessdate=2013-04-09|date=2013-04-08|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> Albrecht scored 17 first-half points on 4-for-4 three-point shooting.<ref name=LoMtwnc>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=330980097|title=Louisville outlasts Michigan to win national championship|accessdate=2013-04-09|date=2013-04-08|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> Albrecht made the seven-man All-Tournament team (which was revised multiple times) along with teammates McGary and [[Trey Burke]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=330980097|title=(4) Michigan 76 (31<U+2013>8, 12<U+2013>6 Big Ten); (1) Louisville 82 (35<U+2013>5, 14<U+2013>4 Big East)|accessdate=2013-04-09|date=2013-04-08|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kake.com/sports/headlines/WSUs-Early-Named-To-Final-Four-All-Tournament-Team-202112911.html|title=WSU's Early Named To Final Four All Tournament Team|accessdate=2013-04-09|date=2013-04-09|publisher=[[KAKE]]}}</ref> When ''[[The New York Times]]'' Sports page did a year in review, Albrecht's picture appeared with a feature story about his 17-point performance (video below).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/30/sports/ncaabasketball/an-underdogs-tale-half-written.html|title=2013: A Look Back, and Beyond: An Underdog's Tale, Half Written|accessdate=2014-01-30|date=2013-12-30|work=[[The New York Times]]|author=Shpigel, Ben}}</ref> [[NBC Sports]] journalist Rob Dauster described the performance as "arguably the most memorable half of basketball you'll ever see".<ref name=WdSAMadfaets>{{cite web|url=http://collegebasketballtalk.nbcsports.com/2013/11/06/what-does-spike-albrecht-michigans-almost-hero-do-for-an-encore-this-season/|title=What does Spike Albrecht, Michigan's almost-hero, do for an encore this season?|accessdate=2014-01-30|date=2013-11-06|publisher=[[NBC Sports]]|author=Dauster, Rob}}</ref> By the end of the first half of the game, Albrecht had tied [[Sam Cassell]] by making his first 9 three point shots in his NCAA tournament games that season, and ''[[USA Today]]'' described Albrecht's place in history as "amongst the most unexpected NCAA heroes in history".<ref name=SAitsNcM>''{{cite web|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/gameon/2013/04/08/spike-albrecht-ncaa-tournament-michigan-louisville/2065457/|title=Spike Albrecht is the surprise NCAA championship MVP|accessdate=2014-01-30|date=2013-04-08|work=[[USA Today]]|author=Chase, Chris}}</ref> Following the championship game, Albrecht gained notoriety for tweeting with reigning [[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue|''Sports Illustrated'' Swimsuit Issue]] [[List of Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue cover models|cover model]] and Michigan fan [[Kate Upton]]. He thanked her for her attendance.<ref name=WdSAMadfaets/><ref>''{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/college/michigan-spike-takes-one-last-shot-kate-upton-article-1.1311863|title=Michigan's Spike Albrecht tweets at Kate Upton after loss to Louisville|accessdate=2014-01-30|date=2013-04-09|work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]]|author=Augustine, Bernie}}</ref>

Albrecht established a career high with 6 [[assist (basketball)|assist]]s as Michigan defeated [[2013<U+2013>14 Houston Baptist Huskies men's basketball team|Houston Baptist]] by 54 points on December 7, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=400503912|title=Houston Baptist 53 (3-6, 1-6 away); (22) Michigan 107 (6-3, 5-1 home)|accessdate=2013-12-07|date=2013-12-07|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/120713aaa.html|title=Postgame Notes: #22 Michigan 107, Houston Baptist 53|accessdate=2013-12-07|date=2013-12-07|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=MGoBlue.com}}</ref> On January 22, 2014, against (#10 [[AP Poll]]/[[Coaches' Poll]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bigten.org/blog/2014/01/wednesda.html|title=Wednesday's Men's Basketball Schedule|accessdate=2014-01-23|date=2014-01-22|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=BigTen.org}}</ref>  [[2013<U+2013>14 Iowa Hawkeyes men's basketball team|Iowa]], Albrecht made his first career start, posting new career highs of 7 assists and 4 [[steal (basketball)|steals]], tying a career high with 3 [[rebound (basketball)|rebounds]] and helping Michigan defeated consecutive ranked opponents for the first time since the [[1996<U+2013>97 Michigan Wolverines men's basketball team|1996<U+2013>97 team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=400509994|title=Michigan tops Iowa, sets up clash of conference unbeatens vs. Spartans|accessdate=2014-01-23|date=2014-01-22|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/012214aai.html|title=Postgame Notes: #21 Michigan 75, #10 Iowa 67|accessdate=2014-01-23|date=2014-01-22|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=MGoBlue}}</ref> Albrecht started in place of [[Derrick Walton]] who had the flu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.michigandaily.com/sports/spike-steps-walton%E2%80%99s-absence|title=Spike steps up in Walton's absence|accessdate=2014-01-26|date=2014-01-22|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|author=Kaufman, Simon}}</ref> During the [[Michigan<U+2013>Michigan State basketball rivalry|Michigan<U+2013>Michigan State rivalry game]] on January 25 against the (#3)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bigten.org/blog/2014/01/saturdays-mens-basketball-results-9.html|title=Saturday's Men's Basketball Results|accessdate=2014-01-26|date=2014-01-25|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=BigTen.org}}</ref> [[2013<U+2013>14 Michigan State Spartans men's basketball team|2013<U+2013>14 Spartans]] at the [[Breslin Student Events Center|Breslin Center]], the Michigan State fans heckled Albrecht when he shot [[free throw]]s with [[Justin Bieber]] chants.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2014/01/michigan-state-fans-mock-michigans-spike-albrecht-with-justin-bieber-chants/|title=Michigan State fans mock Michigan's Spike Albrecht with Justin Bieber chants|accessdate=2014-01-30|date=2014-01-25|work=[[USA Today]]|author=Gleeson, Scott}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/sports/2014/01/michigan-state-fans-chant-justin-bieber|title=Michigan State Fans Chant "Justin Bieber" and Still Lose (Video)|accessdate=2014-01-30|date=2014-01-26|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|author=Josephs, Brian}}</ref>
